From 7789265cb0ab2ae2e35dba500a06774764ed4e14 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Micheal Waltz <micheal@ecliptik.com>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 17:47:43 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] 8.3: rename engine-bundled data files for no-LFN DOS
 compatibility
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Phase 8 LFN-Option-B execution (task #28), companion to 0033 source-
side renames. This patch updates the on-disk filenames in
vendor/nxengine-evo/data/ to match the new 8.3-compliant strings the
source now emits.

Renames in this patch (61 file moves):

  data/StageMeta/                  -> data/StgMeta/         (directory: 9->7 chars)
  data/StgMeta/*.json (×54)        -> data/StgMeta/*.jsn   (extension: 4->3 chars)
  data/music.json                  -> data/music.jsn
  data/music_dirs.json             -> data/musicdir.jsn    (10->8 char stem)
  data/system.json                 -> data/system.jsn
  data/bkHellish.pbm               -> data/bkHellsh.pbm    (9->8 char stem)
  data/endpic/credit01m.bmp        -> data/endpic/credt01m.bmp  (9->8 char stem)
  data/endpic/credit02m.bmp        -> data/endpic/credt02m.bmp
  data/endpic/credit03m.bmp        -> data/endpic/credt03m.bmp

Not renamed in this patch (user-data, not engine-bundled):

  - StageSelect.tsc, ArmsImage.pbm, ItemImage.pbm, StageImage.pbm
    come from the user's Cave Story freeware extract (doukutsu-rs /
    NXExtract / cavestory.one), not vendor/. The required renames
    (StgSel.tsc, ArmImg.pbm, ItmImg.pbm, StgImg.pbm) are documented
    in docs/ASSETS.md for users to apply post-extraction.
  - Npc/NpcBallos.pbm, NpcIsland.pbm, NpcPriest.pbm, NpcStream.pbm
    + Stage/PrtAlmond.pbm, Stage/Almond.pxa — same: user data, see
    ASSETS.md.

Not renamed in this patch (intentional, dead code path):

  - data/bk*480fix.pbm (5 files: Fog/Hellish/Light/Moon/Sunset).
    These are widescreen-only backdrops; the source code path that
    references them (map.cpp:560, "+ 480fix.pbm") is gated on
    Renderer::widescreen, which is forced false on DOS by patch
    0005-renderer-lock-320x240-fullscreen.patch. The 5 files are
    excluded from the staging step instead of being renamed — saves
    5 file deltas + ~2 MB of unused data per CF deploy. Makefile
    change in companion piece outside this patch series.

Companion patches:
  0033 — source-side string-literal + sprintf renames.
  0035 — sprites.sif binary regeneration (sprite-sheet path table).

Why DOS needs this: only DOS without an LFN driver enforces 8.3 at the
filesystem layer. Desktop builds see no functional change.
